biography.content:
Dr. Jaggi Rao is a board-certified dermatologist licensed in both Canada and the United States.  He is also a certified cosmetic and laser surgeon.
Dr. Rao serves as a Clinical Professor of Medicine and the Dermatology Residency Program Director at the University of Alberta, leading the team responsible for training future dermatologists.  
In addition to the daily training of residents, medical students and nurses, Dr. Rao is a very popular speaker for the medical community, delivering dozens of  lectures a year at local, national and international meetings.  He is an an accomplished author, peer reviewer and associate editor for prominent medical journals including Dermatologic Surgery and The Journal of Drugs in Dermatology.  He is a participant on various industry advisory boards, and serves on the Board of Directors for several institutions, including the Canadian Association of Aesthetic Medicine.
Dr. Rao has won numerous clinical, leadership and academic awards.
